♪ Slow down, slow down ♪

21:22.058 --> 21:24.764
♪ Slow down, slow down ♪

21:24.766 --> 21:27.265
♪ Slow down, slow down ♪

21:27.267 --> 21:29.848
♪ Slow down, slow down ♪

21:29.850 --> 21:32.515
♪ Slow down ♪

21:32.517 --> 21:34.017
Well, well, well.

21:38.808 --> 21:40.225
This is nice.

21:47.725 --> 21:49.348
What's this?

21:49.350 --> 21:52.723
That is everything that you
need to know for the story

21:52.725 --> 21:55.265
and then some.

21:55.267 --> 21:57.390
As I said earlier,
this is your exclusive.

21:57.392 --> 21:58.557
You can do
what you want with it.

21:58.559 --> 22:00.056
All that I ask

22:00.058 --> 22:02.350
is that you keep my name
completely out of it.

22:06.517 --> 22:08.557
You know, I...

22:08.559 --> 22:10.140
had a friend who
committed suicide

22:10.142 --> 22:11.681
a few months ago.

22:11.683 --> 22:12.808
Terrence Mitchell.

22:15.475 --> 22:18.723
The truth is,
this is actually my story.

22:18.725 --> 22:21.267
I started my law career
at that firm.

22:24.683 --> 22:28.015
It's just sad to see
that after 25 years,

22:28.017 --> 22:29.683
nothing really has changed.

22:32.058 --> 22:34.225
So I just said enough is enough.

22:39.100 --> 22:42.432
You're more than
welcome to stay,

22:42.434 --> 22:44.015
but whenever you're
ready to head back,

22:44.017 --> 22:45.725
my driver's standing by.

22:48.100 --> 22:50.723
Well,

22:50.725 --> 22:53.681
I'd like to thank you
for an incredibly...

22:53.683 --> 22:55.889
spirited evening

22:55.891 --> 22:58.183
and for entrusting me with this.

23:08.517 --> 23:10.808
Are you seeing anyone
right now?

23:14.808 --> 23:17.806
I have to leave the country
for a couple of days,

23:17.808 --> 23:20.681
but when I get back,
I'd like to sit down and talk

23:20.683 --> 23:22.223
about you and I
seeing one another

23:22.225 --> 23:25.557
and how that might look.

23:25.559 --> 23:28.307
How does that sound to you?

23:28.309 --> 23:30.683
That sounds like something
I might look forward to.

23:32.392 --> 23:34.098
Okay.

23:34.100 --> 23:35.309
That's settled.

23:38.683 --> 23:39.850
Bon appétit.

23:45.225 --> 23:47.100
[elevator chimes]

24:21.142 --> 24:22.806
[knocking on door]

24:22.808 --> 24:25.307
(Patrick) I got to get to work.
What's going on?

24:25.309 --> 24:27.973
Are you stressed?

24:27.975 --> 24:30.307
Uh, yeah.

24:30.309 --> 24:33.390
No, I mean,

24:33.392 --> 24:35.183
have you ever
thought about suicide?

24:38.058 --> 24:41.806
Killing myself?
- Yeah.

24:41.808 --> 24:45.683
I mean, honestly, Patrick,
I don't know how you do it.

24:47.058 --> 24:48.473
But I--

24:48.475 --> 24:51.515
I love you, okay?

24:51.517 --> 24:55.056
I know you and I have had
our moments, but I do love you,

24:55.058 --> 24:58.098
and if you ever need anyone
to talk to, I'm here.

24:58.100 --> 24:59.764
You are not alone.

24:59.766 --> 25:02.889
Please stop me
before I break into song.

25:02.891 --> 25:04.683
You ain't getting
rid of me that easy.

25:07.392 --> 25:09.434
Everything is gonna work
out for you, Patrick.

25:15.267 --> 25:16.934
Then maybe you need
this more than I do.

25:21.267 --> 25:23.015
You brought me all this stuff?

25:23.017 --> 25:25.265
As we continue to follow
the ongoing investigation

25:25.267 --> 25:27.348
of yesterday's tragic suicide,

25:27.350 --> 25:30.307
evidence has emerged to indicate
that not only were the partners

25:30.309 --> 25:31.806
of Durbin, McGee & Marting

25:31.808 --> 25:35.056
Aware of this proud father
of two's despair,

25:35.058 --> 25:37.848
but that they may have been
the very cause of it.

25:37.850 --> 25:40.681
Seen here in an internal memo,

25:40.683 --> 25:42.681
controlling partner
Wallace Marting states,

25:42.683 --> 25:46.056
and I quote, "Tell him"
to bleeping get over it.

25:46.058 --> 25:48.140
We're all unhappy.
That's just life.

25:48.142 --> 25:50.764
It's not like we can fire him
without Al Sharpton showing up

25:50.766 --> 25:53.223
with a bleeping army
throwing the bleeping race card

25:53.225 --> 25:55.015
in our bleeping faces.

25:55.017 --> 25:56.931
The memo continues on to say,

25:56.933 --> 26:00.223
and again I quote, "Get"
what you can out of the bleep.

26:00.225 --> 26:03.098
I'm sure he's just going
to bleeping quit anyway.

26:03.100 --> 26:04.557
This memo was written

26:04.559 --> 26:08.056
a mere three weeks before
Brian Ellis took his life.

26:08.058 --> 26:10.681
As the authorities determine
whether or not criminal charges

26:10.683 --> 26:12.557
should be filed,
I'd like to turn your attention

26:12.559 --> 26:16.557
to a 2014 study from the Center
for Talent Innovation

26:16.559 --> 26:18.889
which reports
that an alarming 40%

26:18.891 --> 26:21.307
of African-Americans
admit to feeling like outsiders

26:21.309 --> 26:22.931
in the corporate culture,

26:22.933 --> 26:25.889
as compared
to 26% of Caucasians.

26:25.891 --> 26:28.390
And despite corporate America's
ongoing attempts to create

26:28.392 --> 26:30.056
a more diverse work environment,

26:30.058 --> 26:31.432
a staggering 35%

26:31.434 --> 26:32.806
of African-Americans claim

26:32.808 --> 26:35.973
that they need to compromise
their authenticity

26:35.975 --> 26:38.098
in order to conform
to their company's standards

26:38.100 --> 26:41.056
of demeanor or style.

26:41.058 --> 26:43.889
When it comes to issues
of equality in the workplace,

26:43.891 --> 26:46.140
it should never be
about black and white.

26:46.142 --> 26:47.432
It should be about right,

26:47.434 --> 26:50.515
and wrong,
and who's getting the job done.

26:50.517 --> 26:52.473
I'm Mary Jane Paul.

26:52.475 --> 26:54.390
Thank you for listening.

26:54.392 --> 26:56.681
And we're clear.
- Nice job, guys.

26:56.683 --> 26:59.681
Reset Sammy back to two.

26:59.683 --> 27:02.056
So much for
impartial reporting.

27:02.058 --> 27:04.181
What the hell was that?
- I'm just stating the facts.

27:04.183 --> 27:07.015
Yeah, well, your mysterious
source's so-called facts

27:07.017 --> 27:08.848
seem a little too
convenient for me.

27:08.850 --> 27:11.056
They checked out, right?
- Well, yeah, they did,

27:11.058 --> 27:12.889
but, I mean, don't you feel

27:12.891 --> 27:14.681
like there's got to be
more to this story?

27:14.683 --> 27:16.515
Why?
Because you didn't write it?

27:16.517 --> 27:17.848
Excuse me?
- I'm sorry.

27:17.850 --> 27:19.848
I'm just tired of
every move I make

27:19.850 --> 27:22.056
being scrutinized
by the entire corporation.

27:22.058 --> 27:25.265
If you're implying that
every decision, every thought,

27:25.267 --> 27:27.557
every breath I take
at this damn network

27:27.559 --> 27:29.432
isn't also being scrutinized,

27:29.434 --> 27:30.848
you are sadly mistaken.

27:30.850 --> 27:33.390
Oh, did they assemble
a secret focus group session

27:33.392 --> 27:35.973
for you as well?

27:35.975 --> 27:37.392
Oh, right.

27:38.725 --> 27:40.392
You thought I didn't know.

27:42.808 --> 27:46.764
I was ordered not to tell you.

27:46.766 --> 27:49.098
I'm sorry, but the last time
I heard that story,

27:49.100 --> 27:50.931
I wound up almost getting fired,

27:50.933 --> 27:52.723
and you wound up
with a promotion.

27:52.725 --> 27:55.764
You know I didn't ask
for any of that stuff with Mark.

27:55.766 --> 27:57.390
And I also know that you
are going through a lot

27:57.392 --> 27:58.931
with this egg freezing,

27:58.933 --> 28:00.764
so I didn't know when
the right time to tell you was.

28:00.766 --> 28:03.390
Ordered not to tell me.

28:03.392 --> 28:06.223
I've been begging Greg
to tell you himself.

28:06.225 --> 28:08.015
I--you know what?

28:08.017 --> 28:09.681
I sound defensive.

28:09.683 --> 28:11.931
Look, I didn't do anything.

28:11.933 --> 28:14.015
I know.

28:14.017 --> 28:16.140
I know.

28:16.142 --> 28:17.434
Not a damn thing.

28:21.267 --> 28:23.015
(Mary Jane) Hey, you.
You watch my show today?

28:23.017 --> 28:25.056
(Val) Well, I've been in
therapy with patients

28:25.058 --> 28:26.265
all afternoon, so--

28:26.267 --> 28:27.764
Ooh, Val, I'm so sorry.

28:27.766 --> 28:29.348
The number came up private.

28:29.350 --> 28:30.764
I thought you were somebody
else. What's up?

28:30.766 --> 28:32.681
(Val) Yeah, I'm sorry
for the random call,

28:32.683 --> 28:36.098
but have you heard
from Lisa recently?

28:36.100 --> 28:38.015
No, not in the last few days.

28:38.017 --> 28:39.973
Well, she left me a message
this morning,

28:39.975 --> 28:41.348
and it was just really strange.

28:41.350 --> 28:43.223
She was going on
about an argument

28:43.225 --> 28:44.681
that the two of you had

28:44.683 --> 28:47.098
and how David
was still in love with you,

28:47.100 --> 28:49.265
and I don't want
to jump to conclusions,

28:49.267 --> 28:50.307
but I'm headed over there.

28:50.309 --> 28:51.931
I've been trying to call her.

28:51.933 --> 28:53.723
She's not answering the phone.
- Okay. I'm on my way.

28:53.725 --> 28:55.017
I'll meet you there.

29:13.975 --> 29:15.764
Don't worry. She's fine.

29:15.766 --> 29:17.473
At least now she is.
- Well, what happened?

29:17.475 --> 29:19.390
Well, she was pretty
disoriented when I got here.

29:19.392 --> 29:21.557
I gave her some meds.
She's upstairs sleeping now.

29:21.559 --> 29:23.181
Okay.

29:23.183 --> 29:25.806
Listen, you've been dealing
with this longer than I have,

29:25.808 --> 29:27.432
and though I'm here as a friend

29:27.434 --> 29:30.265
and not a psychiatrist,
I do need to ask you.

29:30.267 --> 29:32.806
Do you think that she might
be a danger to herself?

29:32.808 --> 29:35.557
Because if you think
that she's suicidal,

29:35.559 --> 29:37.681
then we really should
consider a 5150.

29:37.683 --> 29:40.973
No. No, her career would never
survive a psychiatric hold. No.

29:40.975 --> 29:42.681
Well, don't you think
that being alive

29:42.683 --> 29:44.223
is a little more
important than her career?

29:44.225 --> 29:45.681
Not to Lisa it isn't.
- All right.

29:45.683 --> 29:47.683
Well, what about
when she almost overdosed?

29:49.434 --> 29:52.223
She didn't try
to kill herself, okay?

29:52.225 --> 29:53.681
Maybe she's a little lonely.

29:53.683 --> 29:56.557
A little depressed,
but not suicidal.

29:56.559 --> 29:59.473
How do you even know
about that incident anyway?

29:59.475 --> 30:00.723
David told me...
- Of course.

30:00.725 --> 30:02.848
Of course.
- In confidence.

30:02.850 --> 30:05.848
He was worried, and he wanted
my professional opinion.

